    <record id="red_revolution_tomato_seeds" model="ir.ui.view">
        <field name="name">Red Revolution - Tomato Seeds</field>
        <field name="key">website.red-revolution-tomato-seeds</field>
        <field name="type">qweb</field>
        <field name="website_id" ref="website.default_website"/>
        <field name="arch" type="xml">
            <t t-name="website.red-revolution-tomato-seeds">
                <t t-call="website.layout">
                    <div id="wrap" class="oe_structure oe_empty">
                        <section class="s_picture pb24 pt80 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_picture" data-name="Picture" style="background-image: none;">
                            <div class="container">
                                <h2 style="text-align: center;">Red Revolution - Tomato Seeds</h2>
                                <p style="text-align: center;">
                                    <br/>
                                </p>
                                <div class="row s_nb_column_fixed">
                                    <div class="o_colored_level pb0 col-lg-9 offset-lg-2" style="text-align: center;">
                                        <figure class="figure">
                                            <img src="/web/image/agriculture_shop.ir_attachment_664" alt="" class="figure-img img-thumbnail padding-large img img-fluid o_we_custom_image" data-mimetype="image/webp" data-resize-width="612"/>
                                            <figcaption class="figure-caption text-muted py-3 o_default_snippet_text">
                                                <br/>
                                            </figcaption>
                                        </figure>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                        <section class="s_text_block pt40 pb40 o_colored_level" data-snippet="s_text_block" data-name="Text" style="background-image: none;">
                            <div class="container s_allow_columns">
                                <p class="o_default_snippet_text">Organic tomato seeds are meticulously produced through a natural and environmentally conscious process. It all begins with carefully selected parent plants that are grown without synthetic pesticides, fertilizers, or genetically modified organisms. These parent plants are nurtured in healthy soil, allowing them to develop robust traits and flavors.<br/></p>
                                <p class="o_default_snippet_text">During the flowering phase, skilled growers often employ natural pollination methods, such as encouraging bees and other pollinators to transfer pollen between flowers. This ensures genetic diversity and vitality in the resulting seeds.</p>
                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;">
                                    <br/>
                                </p>
                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;">As the tomatoes ripen and mature, they are harvested at their peak, with a focus on selecting the healthiest and most vigorous fruits. These fruits are carefully processed to extract their seeds, which are then thoroughly cleaned and fermented. Fermentation helps remove the gel-like coating around the seeds, which can inhibit germination.</p>
                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;">
                                    <br/>
                                </p>
                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;">Following fermentation, the seeds are washed, dried naturally, and carefully stored in a controlled environment to maintain their viability. This entire process adheres to the principles of organic farming, promoting ecological balance, biodiversity, and sustainability.</p>
                                <p style="margin-bottom: 0px;">
                                    <br/>
                                </p>
                                <p>The result is a batch of premium organic tomato seeds, ready to be shared with growers and gardeners who are committed to cultivating delicious, nutritious, and environmentally friendly tomato plants.<br/></p>
                            </div>
                        </section>
                    </div>
                </t>
            </t>
        </field>
    </record>
